179 
180 /* Support for Korean(EUC_KR) characters, by powerm90@tinc.co.kr and mrpark@tinc.co.kr */
181 
182 /*
183  Unicode mapping is done according to:
184  ftp://ftp.unicode.org/Public/MAPPINGS/OBSOLETE/EASTASIA/KSC/KSC5601.TXT
185 
186  Valid multi-byte characters:
187 
188  [81..FE][41..5A,61..7A,81..FE]
189 
190  Note, 0x5C is not a valid MB tail,
191  so escape_with_backslash_is_dangerous is not set.
192 */
193 
194 #define iseuc_kr_head(c) ((0x81<=(uchar)(c) && (uchar)(c)<=0xfe))
195 
196 #define iseuc_kr_tail1(c) ((uchar) (c) >= 0x41 && (uchar) (c) <= 0x5A)
197 #define iseuc_kr_tail2(c) ((uchar) (c) >= 0x61 && (uchar) (c) <= 0x7A)
198 #define iseuc_kr_tail3(c) ((uchar) (c) >= 0x81 && (uchar) (c) <= 0xFE)
199 
200 #define iseuc_kr_tail(c) (iseuc_kr_tail1(c) || \
201  iseuc_kr_tail2(c) || \
202  iseuc_kr_tail3(c))
203 
204 
205 static uint ismbchar_euc_kr(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
206  const char* p, const char *e)
207 {
208  return ((*(uchar*)(p)<0x80)? 0:\
209  iseuc_kr_head(*(p)) && (e)-(p)>1 && iseuc_kr_tail(*((p)+1))? 2:\
210  0);
211 }
212 
213 static uint mbcharlen_euc_kr(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),uint c)
214 {
215  return (iseuc_kr_head(c) ? 2 : 1);
216 }

9844 static int func_uni_ksc5601_onechar(int code){
9845  if ((code>=0x00A1)&&(code<=0x0167))
9846  return(tab_uni_ksc56010[code-0x00A1]);
9847  if ((code>=0x02C7)&&(code<=0x0451))
9848  return(tab_uni_ksc56011[code-0x02C7]);
9849  if ((code>=0x2015)&&(code<=0x2312))
9850  return(tab_uni_ksc56012[code-0x2015]);
9851  if ((code>=0x2460)&&(code<=0x266D))
9852  return(tab_uni_ksc56013[code-0x2460]);
9853  if ((code>=0x3000)&&(code<=0x327F))
9854  return(tab_uni_ksc56014[code-0x3000]);
9855  if ((code>=0x3380)&&(code<=0x33DD))
9856  return(tab_uni_ksc56015[code-0x3380]);
9857  if ((code>=0x4E00)&&(code<=0x947F))
9858  return(tab_uni_ksc56016[code-0x4E00]);
9859  if ((code>=0x9577)&&(code<=0x9F9C))
9860  return(tab_uni_ksc56017[code-0x9577]);
9861  if ((code>=0xAC00)&&(code<=0xD7A3))
9862  return(tab_uni_ksc56018[code-0xAC00]);
9863  if ((code>=0xF900)&&(code<=0xFA0B))
9864  return(tab_uni_ksc56019[code-0xF900]);
9865  if ((code>=0xFF01)&&(code<=0xFFE6))
9866  return(tab_uni_ksc560110[code-0xFF01]);
9867  return(0);

9871 static int
9872 my_wc_mb_euc_kr(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
9873  my_wc_t wc, uchar *s, uchar *e)
9874 {
9875  int code;
9876 
9877  if (s >= e)
9878  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL;
9879 
9880  if ((uint) wc < 0x80)
9881  {
9882  s[0]= (uchar) wc;
9883  return 1;
9884  }
9885 
9886  if (!(code=func_uni_ksc5601_onechar(wc)))
9887  return MY_CS_ILUNI;
9888 
9889  if (s+2>e)
9890  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL2;
9891 
9892  s[0]=code>>8;
9893  s[1]=code&0xFF;
9894 
9895  return 2;
9896 }
9897 
9898 
9899 static int
9900 my_mb_wc_euc_kr(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
9901  my_wc_t *pwc, const uchar *s, const uchar *e)
9902 {
9903 
9904  int hi;
9905 
9906  if (s >= e)
9907  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL;
9908 
9909  if ((hi= s[0]) < 0x80)
9910  {
9911  pwc[0]=hi;
9912  return 1;
9913  }
9914 
9915  if (s+2>e)
9916  return MY_CS_TOOSMALL2;
9917 
9918  if (!(pwc[0]=func_ksc5601_uni_onechar((hi<<8)+s[1])))
9919  return -2;
9920 
9921  return 2;
9922 }

9925 /*
9926  Returns well formed length of a EUC-KR string.
9927 */
9928 static size_t
9929 my_well_formed_len_euckr(CHARSET_INFO *cs __attribute__((unused)),
9930  const char *b, const char *e,
9931  size_t pos, int *error)
9932 {
9933  const char *b0= b;
9934  const char *emb= e - 1; /* Last possible end of an MB character */
9935 
9936  *error= 0;
9937  while (pos-- && b < e)
9938  {
9939  if ((uchar) b[0] < 128)
9940  {
9941  /* Single byte ascii character */
9942  b++;
9943  }
9944  else if (b < emb && iseuc_kr_head(*b) && iseuc_kr_tail(b[1]))
9945  {
9946  /* Double byte character */
9947  b+= 2;
9948  }
9949  else
9950  {
9951  /* Wrong byte sequence */
9952  *error= 1;
9953  break;
9954  }
9955  }
9956  return (size_t) (b - b0);
9957 }
